text: They changed so much of the storyline.   Spoilers from the book:  In The Longest Ride, Ira's car getting trapped in the snow made the story more endearing. And, all the conversations he had with Ruth there made it magical (even if it was just his delusions). The car catching fire makes it seem like Ira just gets into an accident that night and they rescue him a few hours after. Probably, meaning no meeting's with a Young Ruth. Sophia met Luke outside of a party at a restored Barn. She never mets up with Ira prior to coming to his rescue (with Luke). From the trailer it looks like Sophia has an office job instead of being a Sorority College Student. I'll still watch it, however. I just hate when only remnants of a story make it to movie adaptions. It's a huge letdown. Details are important to me.
